<topic id="author-display-markup">
  <title>Displaying the Markup</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Author editing mode<indexterm>Displaying the markup</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Displaying markup in Author mode</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Author editing mode<indexterm>Tags Display Mode</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Tags Display Mode</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_t5w_bgk_54b">You can control the amount of markup that is displayed in the <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol>
      mode with various levels of tag modes for both <term>block</term> and <term>in-line</term>
      elements.</p>
    <p id="p_u5w_bgk_54b">The following dedicated tag modes are available from the <uicontrol><image
          href="../img/TagsDrop.png" id="image_pmr_mhm_1s"/>Tags Display Mode</uicontrol> drop-down
      menu (available on the toolbar):</p>
    <p id="p_v5w_bgk_54b">
      <dl conkeyref="reusables-author-actions/dl_Tags_Display_Mode" id="dl_tyj_qbf_tpb">
        <dlentry id="dlentry_uyj_qbf_tpb">
          <dt/>
          <dd/>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
      <note id="note_dvw_bgk_54b">The associated CSS information is used to determine whether a tag should be considered
          <term>inline</term> or <term>block</term>. If the current document does not have an
        associated CSS stylesheet, then the <uicontrol>Full Tags</uicontrol> mode will be
        used.</note>
    </p>
  </body>
